6ï¸âƒ£ Method
ğŸ“Œ A function inside a class that belongs to an object.

âœ” Example:
class Car:
    def __init__(self, brand):
        self.brand = brand

    def show_brand(self):  # Method
        print("Car Brand:", self.brand)

my_car = Car("Honda")
my_car.show_brand()  # Output: Car Brand: Honda



ğŸš€ Final Takeaway
âœ” Objects are instances of classes.
âœ” Variables store data.
âœ” Functions perform tasks.
âœ” Classes create objects.
âœ” Attributes store object data.
âœ” Methods allow objects to perform actions.
